# vi
========================

for editing file content in terminal

[https://www.atmos.albany.edu/daes/atmclasses/atm350/vi_cheat_sheet.pdf](https://www.atmos.albany.edu/daes/atmclasses/atm350/vi_cheat_sheet.pdf)
[https://docs.oracle.com/cd/E19253-01/806-7612/editorvi-62/index.html](https://docs.oracle.com/cd/E19253-01/806-7612/editorvi-62/index.html)

##  Frequently used Commands

`i` to switch to editing mode (insert)
`esc` to switch back to command mode
`/<SEARCH>` - replace <SEARCH> with the word you want to find
`:wq` - (write and quit) save document and quit